1
00:01:10,670 --> 00:01:13,463
Yo, Jimmy. Give me the status.
Tell me we good.

2
00:01:13,548 --> 00:01:15,299
- You got it, man.
- Beautiful.

3
00:01:15,757 --> 00:01:18,510
It's gonna be an all-timer tonight.

4
00:01:22,682 --> 00:01:25,602
All right, fire them up!

5
00:01:26,144 --> 00:01:27,936
We go live in five!

6
00:01:28,938 --> 00:01:32,150
It's time for ignition
and straight automobile pimping.

7
00:02:03,847 --> 00:02:05,724
- Girl!
- Sorry! My bad!

8
00:02:10,646 --> 00:02:13,191
All right, ladies! We're good.

9
00:02:13,983 --> 00:02:15,318
We're good.

10
00:02:16,318 --> 00:02:17,611
That's it, babies.

11
00:02:20,782 --> 00:02:23,241
Come on, Tej!
Let's get this race going!

12
00:02:24,326 --> 00:02:26,037
Wait a second, man.

13
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:28,872
You cats are first wave.
Where's your fourth at?

14
00:02:28,955 --> 00:02:32,085
It was Joaquin, but he had
to work the graveyard shift.

15
00:02:32,168 --> 00:02:34,545
What? Graveyard shift, man.

16
00:02:35,378 --> 00:02:39,300
- Why don't you run with us, Tej?
- Hell, I'm not running with y'all.

17
00:02:39,634 --> 00:02:43,471
I tell you, either you find a fourth
or you don't race. How about that?

18
00:02:43,554 --> 00:02:47,057
We should find two, so we don't have
to roll with skirt here.

19
00:02:52,562 --> 00:02:54,397
Whoa, wait a second.

20
00:02:54,774 --> 00:02:58,527
Why don't I find you a fourth
and we settle this on the streets?

21
00:02:58,610 --> 00:03:00,947
- Bring him on.
- Anybody I want?

22
00:03:01,322 --> 00:03:03,324
No matter who it is?

23
00:03:03,407 --> 00:03:04,574
Yeah.

24
00:03:10,122 --> 00:03:11,206
Yeah?

25
00:03:11,289 --> 00:03:13,209
Yeah, man. You want to race tonight?

26
00:03:13,292 --> 00:03:16,211
I could use the money.
You got four minutes.

27
00:03:16,920 --> 00:03:18,256
I'll be there.

28
00:03:46,158 --> 00:03:48,118
The race starts in four minutes.

29
00:03:49,954 --> 00:03:52,038
All right, girls, let's do this.

30
00:04:03,175 --> 00:04:06,012
- You think you'll win, baby?
- What do you think?

31
00:04:06,888 --> 00:04:09,598
- You better. We got rent to pay.
- I know this.

32
00:04:35,249 --> 00:04:37,959
I'll get you when you
get a car worth racing.

33
00:04:47,136 --> 00:04:48,512
There's our fourth.

34
00:04:48,596 --> 00:04:50,305
Shit. It's Brian.

35
00:05:19,459 --> 00:05:21,836
- What's up, Tej?
- What's happening, dude?

36
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:24,964
- Thanks for the invite.
- No problem at all, man.

37
00:05:25,048 --> 00:05:27,550
Just remember me
when you wax, all right?

38
00:05:28,927 --> 00:05:30,553
They got deep pockets?

39
00:05:31,764 --> 00:05:32,889
Real deep.

40
00:05:35,433 --> 00:05:37,812
- What's up, Suki?
- What's up, Bullitt?

41
00:05:37,894 --> 00:05:39,646
What do you say we kick it a nickel?

42
00:05:41,189 --> 00:05:43,317
Nobody mentioned raising stakes.

43
00:05:49,197 --> 00:05:51,449
If that's the case,
ask these nice people...

44
00:05:51,533 --> 00:05:53,952
to back off the line
so you can go home.

45
00:06:04,963 --> 00:06:07,507
Okay. $3,500.

46
00:06:17,643 --> 00:06:18,894
$3,500?

47
00:06:19,978 --> 00:06:22,230
Either that
or you can go home, bruh.

48
00:06:27,444 --> 00:06:29,612
It's all there.
Better be.

49
00:06:30,781 --> 00:06:34,367
Damn, Suki, when are you
going to pop my clutch?

50
00:06:34,451 --> 00:06:36,620
As soon as you get
the right set of tools.

51
00:06:36,704 --> 00:06:37,954
All right.

52
00:06:58,182 --> 00:07:00,435
All right, back up. Let's go.

53
00:07:02,478 --> 00:07:03,980
Back y'all asses up!

54
00:07:04,064 --> 00:07:06,567
Back up before
you turn into barbecue around here.

55
00:07:06,817 --> 00:07:09,028
It's not a game. This is serious.

56
00:07:09,110 --> 00:07:12,363
All right, back up.
Get off the street. Let's go.

57
00:07:12,531 --> 00:07:16,451
Back it up. Everybody keep
your heads real clear, all right?

58
00:07:16,535 --> 00:07:18,786
'Cause I got a surprise
for y'all this evening.

59
00:07:21,749 --> 00:07:23,709
Go, Slap Jack! Go, baby!

60
00:07:23,792 --> 00:07:25,293
I got this.

61
00:07:34,845 --> 00:07:36,721
Ready?

62
00:07:40,516 --> 00:07:41,685
Go!

63
00:08:32,778 --> 00:08:34,153
Oh, hell, no!

64
00:08:49,168 --> 00:08:51,797
You ain't passing me, dawg. Come on.

65
00:08:54,466 --> 00:08:55,716
What you got?

66
00:09:02,014 --> 00:09:04,017
I told you, you wouldn't pass me!

67
00:09:16,904 --> 00:09:18,157
Move, bitch!

68
00:10:07,246 --> 00:10:08,664
Not tonight, baby!

69
00:10:08,749 --> 00:10:10,667
Bend over, boy.

70
00:10:14,337 --> 00:10:15,589
Damn, girl!

71
00:10:26,850 --> 00:10:28,143
Last turn.

72
00:10:30,854 --> 00:10:31,938
Too wide.

73
00:10:43,450 --> 00:10:44,951
Home stretch, baby.

74
00:10:53,751 --> 00:10:55,128
Got to go, dawg!

75
00:11:14,563 --> 00:11:15,649
Yes!

76
00:11:27,451 --> 00:11:28,495
I can smell you!

77
00:11:28,953 --> 00:11:30,621
Yo, Jimmy, hit it, baby!

78
00:11:36,043 --> 00:11:37,921
All right. Y'all see that?

79
00:11:39,047 --> 00:11:41,006
I told y'all I had a surprise.

80
00:11:41,298 --> 00:11:43,634
How you like that for a finale?

81
00:11:53,102 --> 00:11:54,145
Bridge.

82
00:12:36,187 --> 00:12:37,313
Yeah!

83
00:12:41,610 --> 00:12:42,652
Shit!

84
00:12:52,953 --> 00:12:54,456
Oh, hell, no!

85
00:12:59,628 --> 00:13:01,046
Smack that ass!

86
00:13:25,570 --> 00:13:26,613
Yes!

87
00:13:35,788 --> 00:13:38,750
I saw that, man.
Bullitt and Suki sprayed the bridge.

88
00:13:39,042 --> 00:13:41,753
I need to start making
y'all pay to see this shit.

89
00:13:41,836 --> 00:13:44,588
I got over $10,000
for my man here, all right?

90
00:13:44,923 --> 00:13:47,841
That's what I'm talking about, man.
Play with it.

91
00:13:48,426 --> 00:13:50,803
- Smells good, don't it?
- How about that?

92
00:13:50,886 --> 00:13:53,389
Right. Y'all see this?
Everybody take a good look.

93
00:13:53,472 --> 00:13:56,768
This is what you call mutual
respect. All right, let's clear out.

94
00:13:57,601 --> 00:13:59,604
Anybody down for another race?

95
00:14:00,897 --> 00:14:01,940
Shit.

96
00:14:06,277 --> 00:14:08,989
Make sure you bring that body
by the garage later...

97
00:14:09,072 --> 00:14:12,575
so we can work
on that front end of yours.

98
00:14:13,743 --> 00:14:14,869
Watch out.

99
00:14:15,995 --> 00:14:17,496
Maybe I will.

100
00:14:25,212 --> 00:14:26,755
Where are you going?

101
00:14:27,590 --> 00:14:30,051
- Time to get out of here.
- Why is that?

102
00:15:04,085 --> 00:15:05,794
Nissan Skyline! Got him!

103
00:15:16,096 --> 00:15:17,682
Shit!

104
00:15:41,163 --> 00:15:42,331
Damn!

105
00:15:50,340 --> 00:15:52,549
Let me see your hands!
Put them up!

106
00:15:53,634 --> 00:15:55,345
Yeah, this is him.
We got him.

107
00:16:06,522 --> 00:16:10,567
So, how long
you been in South Florida?

108
00:16:10,652 --> 00:16:12,570
A while.
Before that?

109
00:16:15,865 --> 00:16:18,951
We know you're Brian O'Conner,
formerly of the LAPD.

110
00:16:19,826 --> 00:16:21,913
- You got the wrong guy.
- Really?

111
00:16:26,875 --> 00:16:28,628
How you doing, O'Conner?

112
00:16:31,923 --> 00:16:33,383
Let's take a walk.

113
00:16:36,302 --> 00:16:37,552
Carter Verone.

114
00:16:38,011 --> 00:16:41,224
Born in Argentina, but he's lived
most of his life in Miami.

115
00:16:41,724 --> 00:16:44,811
Now he owns the biggest
import-export business in the state.

116
00:16:44,894 --> 00:16:48,648
Unfortunately, the cartels have been
successful getting drugs into Miami.

117
00:16:48,730 --> 00:16:51,192
But they've had a hard time
getting the cash out.

118
00:16:51,275 --> 00:16:53,068
We've surveilled him for a year.

119
00:16:53,152 --> 00:16:55,863
But we haven't been able to put him
and the money together.

120
00:16:55,947 --> 00:16:58,658
- We've swept his house, warehouses-
- Nothing.

121
00:16:59,116 --> 00:17:02,035
Customs here has done a great job
of getting us this far.

122
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:04,163
I'm here to help get them
over the top.

123
00:17:04,247 --> 00:17:06,540
I was able to get
an agent in undercover...

124
00:17:06,624 --> 00:17:08,875
working travel and
logistics for him.

125
00:17:09,001 --> 00:17:11,628
Verone's put her in charge
of finding new drivers.

126
00:17:11,712 --> 00:17:15,173
Right, although we can't confirm
her status right now.

127
00:17:15,549 --> 00:17:19,136
- You think she's flipped?
- She's one of mine. She's all right.

128
00:17:19,220 --> 00:17:23,307
She's been in with Verone a year.
Even lives at the compound with him.

129
00:17:23,391 --> 00:17:27,519
Look, it was the FBI's idea
to bring you in. I'm against it.

130
00:17:27,811 --> 00:17:31,691
But we need good drivers to put
this asshole and his money together.

131
00:17:31,982 --> 00:17:34,152
You're gonna roll with Agent Dunn.

132
00:17:34,693 --> 00:17:35,987
And if I don't?

133
00:17:36,445 --> 00:17:39,115
Here's a list of the laws
you broke in L.A.

134
00:17:39,531 --> 00:17:42,910
Obstruction of justice, aiding and
abetting. You know the rap sheet.

135
00:17:42,993 --> 00:17:46,580
We can make this all go away
in the interest of justice...

136
00:17:47,330 --> 00:17:49,500
if you're willing to play ball.

137
00:17:52,627 --> 00:17:56,590
What's the idea here? Dunn and I
are supposed to be street racers?

138
00:17:56,715 --> 00:17:58,009
That's right.

139
00:18:04,097 --> 00:18:05,307
So, Dunn...

140
00:18:08,310 --> 00:18:10,563
looks like we're
going to be partners, bro.

141
00:18:10,645 --> 00:18:12,522
Tell me, what would be
a better motor...

142
00:18:12,606 --> 00:18:15,192
for my Skyline,
a Gallo 12 or a Gallo 24?

143
00:18:20,573 --> 00:18:21,824
Twenty four.

144
00:18:22,909 --> 00:18:25,286
I didn't know
pizza places made motors.

145
00:18:28,122 --> 00:18:30,415
See, man, come on, I can't do this.

146
00:18:30,791 --> 00:18:34,961
If this is what you'll give me,
I'll take my chances in Chino.

147
00:18:36,130 --> 00:18:37,839
We'll get someone else.

148
00:18:38,840 --> 00:18:40,300
No way, man.

149
00:18:42,345 --> 00:18:45,640
The only way I'll do this is
if I get to pick the driver.

150
00:18:47,182 --> 00:18:49,852
All right, O'Conner.
Who you got in mind?

151
00:18:50,435 --> 00:18:53,772
- A dude I grew up with in Barstow.
- Who's that?

152
00:18:54,815 --> 00:18:56,107
Roman Pearce.

153
00:19:20,674 --> 00:19:23,385
That him in the Monte Carlo?
That's him.

154
00:19:25,011 --> 00:19:26,888
He's got some skills.

155
00:19:27,222 --> 00:19:29,724
And he's crazy as hell,
I'm telling you.

156
00:19:30,768 --> 00:19:33,186
In a good way, though.
He's the man for the job.

157
00:19:38,358 --> 00:19:41,653
And he has quite a record,
including three years upstate.

158
00:19:42,113 --> 00:19:44,115
Says here,
he's on house arrest now.

159
00:19:44,198 --> 00:19:46,784
Can't go more than
100 yards from his home.

160
00:20:25,071 --> 00:20:27,032
He always said he'd be famous.

161
00:20:31,494 --> 00:20:32,747
Pearce!

162
00:20:33,998 --> 00:20:35,374
Roman Pearce!

163
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:39,336
Whatever happens next,
just let it go.

164
00:20:39,586 --> 00:20:40,837
I ain't in it.

165
00:20:44,090 --> 00:20:45,259
Rome!

166
00:20:51,432 --> 00:20:53,851
Only my homeboys call me Rome...

167
00:20:54,351 --> 00:20:55,478
pig.

168
00:20:59,690 --> 00:21:02,401
- I'm not a cop anymore.
- Is that true?

169
00:21:04,528 --> 00:21:06,196
Blondie here is not a cop anymore?

170
00:21:06,238 --> 00:21:08,574
That's true. No badge.

171
00:21:20,419 --> 00:21:22,046
Here we go.

172
00:21:33,057 --> 00:21:36,018
You still fight like shit.

173
00:21:37,185 --> 00:21:39,020
You better chill.

174
00:21:39,980 --> 00:21:42,398
- Why are you here?
- I'll choke you.

175
00:21:42,482 --> 00:21:44,609
I told you to stay away from me.

176
00:21:48,864 --> 00:21:51,909
You should have told me.
I did three years, Brian.

177
00:21:51,991 --> 00:21:53,701
I told you it wasn't my fault.

178
00:22:03,753 --> 00:22:05,548
Why did you come here?

179
00:22:09,634 --> 00:22:11,303
I got a deal for you.

180
00:22:15,140 --> 00:22:18,184
When I needed your ass,
you were nowhere to be found.

181
00:22:19,894 --> 00:22:22,146
Now you're trying to hand out deals?

182
00:22:25,401 --> 00:22:27,611
I need you to come to Miami
and drive with me.

183
00:22:27,694 --> 00:22:30,990
If you do, they'll take off
that anklet and clear your record.

184
00:22:31,073 --> 00:22:33,200
I did three years in jail.

185
00:22:34,076 --> 00:22:35,994
Three years over you, Brian.

186
00:22:36,996 --> 00:22:39,832
- I know you better than you think.
- Maybe you don't.

187
00:22:39,914 --> 00:22:41,458
Maybe you don't.

188
00:22:42,334 --> 00:22:43,876
You guys finished?

189
00:22:44,752 --> 00:22:46,422
Is this deal legit?

190
00:22:47,006 --> 00:22:49,508
That's right.
If you do this job for us.

191
00:22:49,842 --> 00:22:52,094
- I told you.
- Shut up, punk.

192
00:22:53,886 --> 00:22:57,682
So you'll clean my record
and get this thing off my ankle.

193
00:22:57,766 --> 00:22:59,058
That's right.

194
00:22:59,643 --> 00:23:02,938
I thought you couldn't wander
more than 100 yards from your home.

195
00:23:03,021 --> 00:23:05,606
Why do you think
I'm parked so close to the derby?

196
00:23:05,691 --> 00:23:08,027
Quit playing
like you'll pass this up.

197
00:23:09,653 --> 00:23:11,195
You stupid...

198
00:23:40,808 --> 00:23:42,144
Wait. Hold on.

199
00:23:44,563 --> 00:23:46,230
Bro, what's going on?

200
00:23:46,898 --> 00:23:49,567
I don't know if
I should be trusting you, man.

201
00:23:52,653 --> 00:23:56,741
Think of it this way. It's a chance
for a fresh start. Let's do this.

202
00:23:56,825 --> 00:23:59,869
I wouldn't need a fresh start
if it wasn't for you.

203
00:24:00,203 --> 00:24:02,455
You've been using that
since you got busted.

204
00:24:02,538 --> 00:24:05,917
- Let's just chill out and do this.
- I don't need to chill out.

205
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:09,296
Yes, you do. And you need to stop
blaming me for your mistakes.

206
00:24:09,378 --> 00:24:12,673
Roman Pearce needs to start taking
responsibility for his actions.

207
00:24:12,758 --> 00:24:16,303
- You need to go to hell.
- You need to go back to Barstow.

208
00:24:19,013 --> 00:24:21,349
I'm not going back
to Barstow.

209
00:24:31,984 --> 00:24:35,404
Brian O'Conner,
Roman Pearce, meet Monica Fuentes.

210
00:24:35,489 --> 00:24:38,241
- They have background on Verone?
- They've been briefed.

211
00:24:38,325 --> 00:24:40,618
Good.
All right, here's the deal.

212
00:24:40,701 --> 00:24:43,788
Verone's looking for drivers.
I arranged for you two to join.

213
00:24:43,872 --> 00:24:46,165
I also hired some thugs
to make it legit.

214
00:24:46,250 --> 00:24:48,417
- When do we start?
- Right now.

215
00:24:48,876 --> 00:24:50,420
What are we driving?

216
00:24:57,719 --> 00:25:00,638
Don't even think about
taking the convertible.

217
00:25:00,721 --> 00:25:02,682
It might loosen your mousse.

218
00:25:02,932 --> 00:25:05,644
That's cool.
Too much chrome for me anyways.

219
00:25:05,727 --> 00:25:10,356
Damn! Where do you all
confiscate these rims from, man?

220
00:25:10,982 --> 00:25:13,234
Check in with us after you meet him.

221
00:25:14,819 --> 00:25:17,865
- You okay with these knuckleheads?
- I can handle them.

222
00:25:17,948 --> 00:25:20,992
- If they trouble you, let me know.
- Thanks, Markham.

223
00:25:24,413 --> 00:25:26,080
I ride with you, cowboy.

224
00:25:26,748 --> 00:25:28,291
Why she gotta ride with you?

225
00:25:28,375 --> 00:25:30,544
You get the convertible.
Let's go.

226
00:25:45,057 --> 00:25:46,434
Turn right here.

227
00:25:51,022 --> 00:25:53,608
- So, you used to be a cop?
- Yeah.

228
00:25:55,277 --> 00:25:57,028
How long you been under?

229
00:25:57,863 --> 00:25:59,197
I lost track.

230
00:26:00,031 --> 00:26:01,282
You all right?

231
00:26:03,326 --> 00:26:06,454
You might want to keep
your eyes on the road, playboy.

232
00:26:06,829 --> 00:26:09,833
- You think we're gonna crash?
- I haven't decided yet.

233
00:26:14,671 --> 00:26:16,506
What are you doing, Brian?

234
00:26:26,223 --> 00:26:29,769
He did the "stare and drive" on you,
didn't he? He got that from me.

235
00:27:05,137 --> 00:27:07,473
Once we get in here,
you're on your own.

236
00:27:19,361 --> 00:27:20,778
Look at that one.

237
00:27:21,195 --> 00:27:24,490
Where'd you get them cars?
At the bottom of a cereal box?

238
00:27:26,701 --> 00:27:28,744
Real funny, Fonzie.

239
00:27:30,163 --> 00:27:31,330
Ass.

240
00:27:31,539 --> 00:27:34,291
Roberto, Enrique,
I need pictures of the drivers...

241
00:27:34,375 --> 00:27:37,211
their license plates, cars,
and anything else you can find.

242
00:27:50,267 --> 00:27:51,601
Let's go.

243
00:27:54,604 --> 00:27:57,356
Keep your mouth shut
and follow my lead, all right?

244
00:27:57,440 --> 00:28:00,442
- I got this.
- No, I'm serious.

245
00:28:01,819 --> 00:28:04,196
Handle your business.
I'll handle mine.

246
00:28:07,909 --> 00:28:09,702
Watch your hands, bruh.

247
00:28:12,747 --> 00:28:14,082
Go in line.

248
00:28:14,164 --> 00:28:15,625
Let's go.

249
00:28:24,800 --> 00:28:25,969
Carter.

