752
01:07:55,291 --> 01:08:00,005
Put down the gun!

753
01:08:00,965 --> 01:08:02,590
Enough.

754
01:08:02,967 --> 01:08:04,842
Shut up.

755
01:08:06,554 --> 01:08:08,347
It's over. Come on.

756
01:08:08,847 --> 01:08:10,391
It's over. Let's go.

757
01:08:11,391 --> 01:08:13,686
It's our gun. Come on, let's go.

758
01:08:18,983 --> 01:08:21,694
I'm glad to see you boys
are getting along so well...

759
01:08:21,777 --> 01:08:26,532
because tomorrow, Roberto and
Enrique'll be riding along with you.

760
01:08:26,990 --> 01:08:29,076
Just so we don't have any problems.

761
01:08:29,158 --> 01:08:31,078
I'll see you guys in a bit.

762
01:08:34,957 --> 01:08:37,083
What the hell
was she doing in there?

763
01:08:47,845 --> 01:08:50,096
Where'd you go this morning?

764
01:08:50,221 --> 01:08:52,765
I went to breakfast
with some friends.

765
01:08:58,479 --> 01:08:59,981
With friends?

766
01:09:01,942 --> 01:09:04,069
I do have friends, Carter.

767
01:09:10,743 --> 01:09:11,909
Okay.

768
01:09:13,912 --> 01:09:15,456
I'll see you later.

769
01:09:24,797 --> 01:09:26,216
Nice shirt, Bilkins.

770
01:09:26,300 --> 01:09:27,967
It's my day off.

771
01:09:30,054 --> 01:09:31,764
Well, anyhow, this is the deal.

772
01:09:32,305 --> 01:09:35,641
Last night, Verone threatened a cop
into giving us a window.

773
01:09:35,725 --> 01:09:39,020
We're driving to an airstrip
in the Keys, off Nallwood Avenue.

774
01:09:39,104 --> 01:09:41,731
Verone has a plane there
and he's taking off for good.

775
01:09:41,814 --> 01:09:43,692
Wait a minute. How do you know this?

776
01:09:43,984 --> 01:09:45,234
Monica.

777
01:09:45,652 --> 01:09:48,447
She's doing her job. She warned us.

778
01:09:48,529 --> 01:09:49,989
She warned you about what?

779
01:09:50,073 --> 01:09:52,533
Verone plans to kill us
after we give him the money.

780
01:09:52,618 --> 01:09:55,996
Driving into an ambush
wasn't the deal. I'm calling it off.

781
01:09:56,079 --> 01:09:59,416
Like hell you are.
This is a Customs case, Bilkins.

782
01:09:59,500 --> 01:10:01,667
No one's calling this off
unless I do.

783
01:10:01,752 --> 01:10:03,587
Look, this is real simple.

784
01:10:04,128 --> 01:10:08,466
Make the run, get Verone and his
cash together, so I can move in.

785
01:10:08,550 --> 01:10:11,761
You don't, I'll file enough charges
on you to make you disappear.

786
01:10:11,845 --> 01:10:13,262
Take these.

787
01:10:13,346 --> 01:10:16,766
We're gonna have GPS on you
so you don't get any cute ideas.

788
01:10:16,850 --> 01:10:19,019
And to make sure
nothing happens to them, right?

789
01:10:19,101 --> 01:10:20,561
Yeah, right.

790
01:10:29,404 --> 01:10:31,155
That guy's a dick.

791
01:10:34,201 --> 01:10:36,161
Let me get this right.

792
01:10:36,537 --> 01:10:39,122
If we don't do this,
then we go to jail.

793
01:10:39,497 --> 01:10:42,458
But if we do it,
then Verone's going to kill us.

794
01:10:42,626 --> 01:10:45,712
- It's a hell of a deal, huh?
- Yeah.

795
01:10:47,296 --> 01:10:48,756
Maybe it is.

796
01:10:50,300 --> 01:10:54,637
This guy's got an ass full of loot
that he's ready to dump in our cars.

797
01:10:54,971 --> 01:10:59,141
I can think of two reasons why
he doesn't need that money anymore.

798
01:10:59,225 --> 01:11:00,601
Here we go.

799
01:11:00,685 --> 01:11:02,104
You and me.

800
01:11:02,311 --> 01:11:03,939
Just like the old days.

801
01:11:04,021 --> 01:11:08,318
- What do you think?
- They messed with the wrong guys.

802
01:11:11,445 --> 01:11:13,657
- Tej, what's up, bro?
- What's up?

803
01:11:13,739 --> 01:11:15,367
How quickly can you organise?

804
01:11:15,449 --> 01:11:18,244
Look, if y'all really want
to carry out this plan...

805
01:11:18,328 --> 01:11:21,789
this is the best place to do it.
What do y'all think?

806
01:11:21,872 --> 01:11:24,458
I think it's perfect.
So, what do they store here?

807
01:11:30,465 --> 01:11:31,800
This thing is clean.

808
01:11:31,882 --> 01:11:33,092
Distributor cap.

809
01:11:47,774 --> 01:11:52,612
Jimmy, do we have any half-empty
bottles of nitrous lying around?

810
01:11:52,695 --> 01:11:54,780
Sure, but I've already
loaded you for spray.

811
01:11:54,864 --> 01:11:57,533
I'm thinking we may need it
for something else...

812
01:11:57,617 --> 01:12:00,412
'cause our cars may get
a little crowded, you know?

813
01:12:08,753 --> 01:12:11,297
When did you start eating so much?

814
01:12:12,298 --> 01:12:14,176
I was in jail, bruh.

815
01:12:14,509 --> 01:12:17,345
I know how shitty the grub is
on the inside.

816
01:12:18,471 --> 01:12:21,099
The way things are shaping up
out here right now...

817
01:12:21,182 --> 01:12:24,394
it'll be a matter of time
before I'm back in there, or dead.

818
01:12:25,895 --> 01:12:28,899
So I'm trying to eat all I can
while I can.

819
01:12:30,524 --> 01:12:33,819
Plus, the doctor tells me
I got a high metabolism.

820
01:12:38,533 --> 01:12:40,534
You remember us growing up?

821
01:12:41,118 --> 01:12:43,412
Playing football in the dirt?

822
01:12:44,288 --> 01:12:47,708
Getting into trouble.
All the stupid things we did?

823
01:12:48,918 --> 01:12:51,921
When you got busted,
whether I was a cop or not...

824
01:12:52,005 --> 01:12:54,256
if there was anything
I could have done...

825
01:12:55,132 --> 01:12:57,010
I would have done it.

826
01:12:57,594 --> 01:12:59,762
I just want you to know that.

827
01:13:00,387 --> 01:13:02,890
Is that why
you let that dude go in L.A.?

828
01:13:05,143 --> 01:13:07,854
Yeah, I think
that had a lot to do with it.

829
01:13:10,106 --> 01:13:11,942
When I got busted...

830
01:13:12,525 --> 01:13:13,693
it wasn't your fault.

831
01:13:14,903 --> 01:13:18,198
It was all on me, Mr. Roman Pearce.

832
01:13:18,782 --> 01:13:20,826
Wild and out. Crazy man.

833
01:13:21,868 --> 01:13:24,037
No one could tell me nothing.

834
01:13:24,121 --> 01:13:25,579
Riding solo.

835
01:13:26,206 --> 01:13:27,666
Yeah, well, not anymore.

836
01:13:33,421 --> 01:13:35,131
Not anymore, bro.

837
01:14:00,489 --> 01:14:02,783
I've got Verone's Navigator
leaving the residence.

838
01:14:02,868 --> 01:14:04,034
Copy.

839
01:14:04,743 --> 01:14:07,247
Sir, we've got Verone on the move
to the airstrip.

840
01:14:07,329 --> 01:14:10,125
Let's get a bird in the air.
Tell him to keep his distance.

841
01:14:12,752 --> 01:14:14,212
- Ready.
- Thanks.

842
01:14:15,921 --> 01:14:17,966
- You're all set.
- Thanks.

843
01:14:18,550 --> 01:14:21,219
- All set?
- Yeah. Let's do it.

844
01:14:24,305 --> 01:14:25,556
Report.

845
01:14:27,809 --> 01:14:29,935
What's going on
out there?

846
01:14:31,563 --> 01:14:32,771
Team One, checking in.

847
01:14:32,855 --> 01:14:35,567
- Team Two, checking in.
- Team Three, checking in.

848
01:14:35,649 --> 01:14:37,819
Team Four,
all clear here, too.

849
01:14:38,360 --> 01:14:40,279
Team Five, checking in.

850
01:14:41,072 --> 01:14:42,907
Team Six, all clear.

851
01:14:48,329 --> 01:14:51,041
- Here we go.
- Yeah, so you know what to do.

852
01:14:51,123 --> 01:14:53,167
Stay cool. Keep focused.

853
01:14:53,542 --> 01:14:56,128
Remember the airstrip's
off Nallwood Avenue.

854
01:14:56,212 --> 01:14:58,465
It's the third exit
after the bridge.

855
01:15:00,132 --> 01:15:01,384
Got it.

856
01:15:01,509 --> 01:15:03,427
You ready for this?

857
01:15:03,511 --> 01:15:07,140
Come on, man.
Guns, murderers, and crooked cops?

858
01:15:07,306 --> 01:15:09,059
I was made for this, bruh!

859
01:15:44,719 --> 01:15:46,011
Come on.

860
01:16:09,618 --> 01:16:12,622
I got activity
at Verone's trailer property.

861
01:16:13,038 --> 01:16:15,917
Do not move an inch
until I tell you to!

862
01:16:40,899 --> 01:16:42,193
Load up.

863
01:16:45,029 --> 01:16:46,280
All units...

864
01:16:46,363 --> 01:16:49,408
move on the trailer property.
Right now! Move!

865
01:16:56,332 --> 01:16:59,252
Shit. Local P.D.
is moving in on our guys.

866
01:16:59,668 --> 01:17:02,171
- Three bags in one car?
- Guess so.

867
01:17:15,560 --> 01:17:16,895
The cops.

868
01:17:21,189 --> 01:17:22,609
I am not going back to jail.

869
01:17:22,692 --> 01:17:24,860
Where are you going, man? Let's go!

870
01:17:26,237 --> 01:17:27,947
What is he doing?

871
01:17:49,385 --> 01:17:52,846
Now let's get the chopper over them.
I want eyes right on top.

872
01:17:52,930 --> 01:17:54,015
You got it.

873
01:17:54,097 --> 01:17:55,140
Lima 2-5...

874
01:17:55,224 --> 01:17:56,768
follow GPS.

875
01:18:05,109 --> 01:18:07,444
Do you know what you're doing?

876
01:18:10,530 --> 01:18:12,949
Stay with me, Rome. Come on, man.

877
01:18:21,250 --> 01:18:23,752
I've got them heading south
on I-95.

878
01:18:23,836 --> 01:18:25,921
Bring in the aerial ESDs.

879
01:18:35,555 --> 01:18:36,724
Oh, shit!

880
01:18:40,060 --> 01:18:42,939
- They're catching up, man!
- Shut up, man!

881
01:18:54,699 --> 01:18:56,493
Nice driving, Rome.

882
01:18:56,702 --> 01:18:58,412
I got you, Brian.

883
01:19:03,542 --> 01:19:05,043
Check it out!

884
01:19:17,597 --> 01:19:19,141
What was that?

885
01:19:29,777 --> 01:19:30,944
Oh, shit!

886
01:19:44,708 --> 01:19:47,377
- Come on, man. Take the wheel.
- No. I can't drive.

887
01:19:47,461 --> 01:19:50,756
Just hold the wheel!
Put your hands on it! Hold steady!

888
01:19:54,510 --> 01:19:56,304
What are you doing, man?

889
01:20:51,024 --> 01:20:52,359
Yeah, man!

890
01:21:08,376 --> 01:21:09,542
Hold.

891
01:21:12,087 --> 01:21:14,547
Bilkins, the bird's in place.

892
01:21:18,386 --> 01:21:19,552
Yeah.

893
01:21:21,346 --> 01:21:22,681
We've got Verone's Navigator.

894
01:21:22,765 --> 01:21:25,685
All right. Money's in transit.
Sit tight.

895
01:22:10,229 --> 01:22:12,355
You're a good driver, man.

896
01:22:12,439 --> 01:22:14,442
Thanks, bro.

897
01:22:19,320 --> 01:22:23,242
We've got the area blocked ahead.
They've got nowhere to go.

898
01:22:32,333 --> 01:22:33,877
What was that?

899
01:22:34,670 --> 01:22:35,880
I've got a visual.

900
01:22:36,546 --> 01:22:38,673
Video should be coming through.

901
01:22:38,756 --> 01:22:40,634
I got it. Looks good.

902
01:22:42,261 --> 01:22:44,137
Where are they going?

903
01:22:52,438 --> 01:22:53,605
Shit.

904
01:22:58,985 --> 01:23:02,280
All right, Miami's finest,
let's see what you got.

905
01:23:02,989 --> 01:23:05,158
Come on. Stay with me, boys.

906
01:23:11,164 --> 01:23:13,500
Hey, man, everyone's here.
Time for the show.

907
01:23:13,583 --> 01:23:15,502
Let's give it to them.

908
01:23:19,756 --> 01:23:22,635
All right, let the party begin.
Let's go!

909
01:23:41,444 --> 01:23:44,907
This is unit 25-99.
We have the suspects surrounded.

910
01:24:36,708 --> 01:24:38,085
Holy shit!

911
01:24:44,091 --> 01:24:46,592
It's a scramble, baby! A big one!

912
01:24:52,557 --> 01:24:54,393
Yeah! Let's do this!

913
01:25:02,400 --> 01:25:03,985
Check this out.

914
01:25:12,286 --> 01:25:14,037
We're not tracking them
on the video.

915
01:25:14,121 --> 01:25:16,582
We must have lost them
in the scramble.

916
01:25:16,664 --> 01:25:18,332
Yo, let's break.

917
01:25:19,792 --> 01:25:20,961
Yeah!

918
01:26:04,128 --> 01:26:06,465
All right, we got them going west
on Beach.

919
01:26:06,547 --> 01:26:08,675
Roger that! I've got them!

920
01:26:20,770 --> 01:26:24,106
Customs has a fix on two cars
going west on Beach.

921
01:26:24,524 --> 01:26:26,359
Roger. Follow those cars.

922
01:26:26,443 --> 01:26:27,860
Roger that.

923
01:26:49,966 --> 01:26:51,134
Shit.

924
01:26:52,176 --> 01:26:53,886
They're cornered.

925
01:26:58,140 --> 01:27:00,851
Keep your hands
where I can see them!

926
01:27:00,935 --> 01:27:02,270
Hands up!

927
01:27:02,813 --> 01:27:06,733
I know my tags are out of date,
but damn.

928
01:27:14,908 --> 01:27:16,451
What the hell?

929
01:27:17,786 --> 01:27:19,371
Where are they?

930
01:27:41,475 --> 01:27:42,978
How about them apples, man?

931
01:27:43,060 --> 01:27:46,148
Yeah! That's some driving
for your ass, baby!

932
01:27:47,565 --> 01:27:48,649
Good job, man.

933
01:27:48,734 --> 01:27:50,735
- What are you talking about?
- Whatever.

934
01:27:50,819 --> 01:27:52,779
You're supposed to be
a stone-faced killer!

935
01:27:52,863 --> 01:27:54,698
You were grabbing your seat belt!

936
01:27:54,780 --> 01:27:58,284
Hey, Tej, thanks a lot, bro.
You're clutch. I owe you big time.

937
01:27:58,368 --> 01:28:02,037
Yeah, Brian, you really do owe me.
You really do...

938
01:28:02,913 --> 01:28:03,957
Us.

939
01:28:04,166 --> 01:28:06,585
Suki says you owe us, all right?

940
01:28:08,962 --> 01:28:11,547
- Rome, you there? Come in.
- What's up, man?

941
01:28:11,631 --> 01:28:13,800
Looks like we got
just one trick left.

942
01:28:13,884 --> 01:28:16,595
My pleasure, buddy!
Let's do it, baby!

943
01:28:17,554 --> 01:28:19,765
Maybe we should grab Verone
while we still can.

944
01:28:19,847 --> 01:28:21,307
No! Not yet!

945
01:28:23,435 --> 01:28:24,603
What?

946
01:28:24,685 --> 01:28:25,811
You lost them?

947
01:28:25,895 --> 01:28:27,063
Shit!

948
01:28:27,271 --> 01:28:28,731
Those little pricks are running!

949
01:28:28,814 --> 01:28:30,567
It's your call.
What do you want to do?

950
01:28:30,649 --> 01:28:33,194
We're gonna take him down.
He is not leaving here.

951
01:28:33,819 --> 01:28:35,572
Enjoying the ride?

952
01:28:36,573 --> 01:28:38,240
It's a fast car, huh?

953
01:28:40,034 --> 01:28:42,203
It's a classic. Old school.

954
01:28:42,662 --> 01:28:44,331
American muscle.

955
01:28:46,416 --> 01:28:50,002
This car can do all kinds of things.
Want to see?

956
01:28:51,921 --> 01:28:54,048
Check this out right here, homey.

957
01:28:54,131 --> 01:28:56,426
Hey, what are you doing,
man?

958
01:29:05,976 --> 01:29:07,479
Ejecto seato!

959
01:29:08,145 --> 01:29:10,481
It worked! I love this button!

960
01:29:12,859 --> 01:29:14,610
Stay on your toes!

961
01:29:15,737 --> 01:29:19,198
Mr. O'Conner, it worked!
Blow and go. I'm all clear.

962
01:29:19,448 --> 01:29:21,993
Meet me at the point!
Hurry up! It's on!

963
01:29:22,077 --> 01:29:23,161
All right. 10-4, man.

964
01:29:23,244 --> 01:29:25,079
Are you ready? Let's go!

965
01:29:35,465 --> 01:29:38,176
Let me see your hands!

966
01:29:38,260 --> 01:29:39,511
Freeze!

967
01:29:40,302 --> 01:29:41,512
Clear!

968
01:29:47,894 --> 01:29:51,730
- It's not Verone and Fuentes.
- What do you mean?

969
01:29:51,981 --> 01:29:52,940
Then where the hell are they?

970
01:30:00,532 --> 01:30:02,574
Get off at Tarpon Point.

971
01:30:03,326 --> 01:30:06,662
Tarpon Point?
There's no airstrip at Tarpon Point.

972
01:30:07,497 --> 01:30:10,125
Who said anything about an airstrip?

973
01:30:23,304 --> 01:30:24,514
Brian?

974
01:30:25,222 --> 01:30:27,057
What's the hold-up, bro?

975
01:30:27,266 --> 01:30:29,769
Yo. There's a new plan.
What the hell?

976
01:30:29,853 --> 01:30:33,273
We meet him at Tarpon Point exit,
not the airstrip.

977
01:30:33,355 --> 01:30:36,775
- So, what are you saying?
- Like I said, there's a new plan.

978
01:30:39,112 --> 01:30:40,320
Brian?

979
01:30:40,863 --> 01:30:42,907
Brian? Hello, you there?

980
01:30:44,993 --> 01:30:46,077
Damn!

981
01:30:46,161 --> 01:30:47,619
What the hell is he doing?

982
01:30:47,703 --> 01:30:49,372
The feds are in the wrong place.

983
01:30:49,456 --> 01:30:51,623
Brian's woman is on her own
with Verone.

984
01:30:51,707 --> 01:30:52,751
So...

985
01:30:52,833 --> 01:30:54,752
So Brian's not coming!

986
01:31:10,894 --> 01:31:12,936
- Let him out.
- Get out.

987
01:31:20,569 --> 01:31:21,695
Pop the trunk.

988
01:31:24,157 --> 01:31:25,492
Hurry up.

989
01:31:41,006 --> 01:31:42,257
Where's the rest?

990
01:31:42,341 --> 01:31:44,260
- The other car.
- Another car?

991
01:31:44,719 --> 01:31:47,137
- Where's the other car?
- On its way.

992
01:31:47,221 --> 01:31:48,931
- On the way?
- Yeah.

993
01:31:50,140 --> 01:31:51,391
Here's your money.

994
01:31:51,475 --> 01:31:54,813
So you know nothing about the agents
that stormed my jet?

995
01:32:01,694 --> 01:32:05,198
The funny thing is, I only told
one person about the airstrip.

996
01:32:19,587 --> 01:32:23,257
Customs agents sure
are getting pretty, aren't they?

997
01:32:27,554 --> 01:32:29,305
Put her on the boat.

998
01:32:31,390 --> 01:32:33,560
- Let's go.
- Get on the boat.

999
01:32:48,032 --> 01:32:50,158
Hide the cars and get rid of him.

1000
01:32:50,243 --> 01:32:51,743
Back in the car.

1001
01:33:19,439 --> 01:33:20,814
End of the road.

1002
01:33:23,275 --> 01:33:24,694
You know, I like you.

1003
01:33:24,777 --> 01:33:27,738
But I still got to kill you.
It's my job.

1004
01:33:31,326 --> 01:33:32,659
What's that?

1005
01:33:34,119 --> 01:33:35,704
It's Barstow, baby!

1006
01:33:36,079 --> 01:33:37,789
It's about to get ugly!

1007
01:33:45,756 --> 01:33:47,132
Let's go.

1008
01:34:23,002 --> 01:34:24,252
Come on.

1009
01:34:50,779 --> 01:34:52,198
You had me.

1010
01:34:54,367 --> 01:34:55,827
You slipped.

1011
01:34:57,161 --> 01:34:59,913
Eleven and a half months,
and you slipped once.

1012
01:35:01,289 --> 01:35:03,083
Put her downstairs.

1013
01:35:09,215 --> 01:35:10,882
See you in a second.

1014
01:35:16,680 --> 01:35:18,015
I thought you was dead.

1015
01:35:18,099 --> 01:35:20,268
Me, too. Thanks for saving my ass.

1016
01:35:20,350 --> 01:35:21,644
What are you doing?

1017
01:35:21,726 --> 01:35:25,064
If Verone sees a helicopter
or Customs boat, she's dead!

1018
01:35:25,146 --> 01:35:26,148
Boat.

1019
01:35:26,481 --> 01:35:28,067
Car. Boat.

1020
01:35:28,484 --> 01:35:30,987
You're not gonna do
what I think you're gonna do?

1021
01:35:31,069 --> 01:35:34,073
- Yeah, I think so. You got my back?
- Yeah.

1022
01:35:34,155 --> 01:35:35,533
All right, put on the seat belt.

1023
01:35:35,615 --> 01:35:37,409
Show him some Dukes of Hazzard shit!

1024
01:35:37,493 --> 01:35:40,246
We're gonna do this big!
Hold on, Rome!

1025
01:35:46,752 --> 01:35:48,421
Brian, you're crazy, man!

1026
01:35:48,503 --> 01:35:50,256
What the hell are you doing?

1027
01:36:16,114 --> 01:36:17,867
I think I broke my arm.

1028
01:36:30,755 --> 01:36:32,213
Get the gun.

1029
01:36:53,152 --> 01:36:54,737
It's over, Carter.

1030
01:37:01,786 --> 01:37:03,037
You okay?

1031
01:37:03,203 --> 01:37:04,371
Yeah!

1032
01:37:05,663 --> 01:37:06,748
I'm great.

1033
01:37:13,046 --> 01:37:14,715
We got him, man.

1034
01:37:15,632 --> 01:37:18,219
We got him. Let's get out of here.

1035
01:37:38,322 --> 01:37:39,739
Go, go.

1036
01:37:48,998 --> 01:37:50,583
That ought to do it.

1037
01:37:51,252 --> 01:37:54,838
So, there were three bags total?
The three from the boat?

1038
01:37:55,840 --> 01:37:57,675
So we're good, right?

1039
01:37:58,050 --> 01:37:59,385
Our records are clean?

1040
01:37:59,467 --> 01:38:01,136
You held up your end.

1041
01:38:01,720 --> 01:38:03,389
Your records are clean.

1042
01:38:21,532 --> 01:38:23,868
So maybe there were six bags.

1043
01:38:24,827 --> 01:38:26,828
I guess we can call it even.

1044
01:38:27,078 --> 01:38:28,413
Agent Dunn?

1045
01:38:32,710 --> 01:38:34,627
We found some more evidence.

1046
01:38:37,046 --> 01:38:38,716
Let's take it inside.

1047
01:38:42,720 --> 01:38:44,971
Don't drop the soap, big homey.

1048
01:38:47,307 --> 01:38:50,728
I hope you know when he gets out,
he's going to kill your ass.

1049
01:38:52,061 --> 01:38:53,896
He ain't getting out.

1050
01:38:55,524 --> 01:38:56,942
I'll see you soon.

1051
01:38:57,484 --> 01:39:00,487
- You think he's going to get out?
- He'll be out.

1052
01:39:01,697 --> 01:39:04,073
Not for real.
You think he's getting out?

1053
01:39:04,742 --> 01:39:07,243
We took care of your decoys.
They're free and clear.

1054
01:39:07,328 --> 01:39:09,622
There's a sedan
out on the road for you.

1055
01:39:09,704 --> 01:39:11,873
Try to bring it back in one piece.

1056
01:39:13,958 --> 01:39:16,462
Thanks a lot, Bilkins.
You're all right.

1057
01:39:17,462 --> 01:39:19,172
Thanks for looking out.

1058
01:39:21,634 --> 01:39:23,510
Do you trust me now?

1059
01:39:23,636 --> 01:39:25,136
You're all right.

1060
01:39:29,600 --> 01:39:30,768
Sorry.

1061
01:39:32,144 --> 01:39:34,063
Nice working with you, O'Conner.

1062
01:39:34,188 --> 01:39:35,521
Same here.

1063
01:39:47,784 --> 01:39:51,872
I might have to stay here in Miami,
and keep you out of trouble, bruh.

1064
01:39:54,666 --> 01:39:56,502
You know what I'm talking about.

1065
01:39:56,585 --> 01:39:58,753
You're going to kick it
in Miami?

1066
01:39:59,128 --> 01:40:02,173
I love Miami.
Miami is off the hook!

1067
01:40:04,342 --> 01:40:06,386
Open a garage together.

1068
01:40:07,179 --> 01:40:10,015
A garage?
How are we going to do that?

1069
01:40:14,895 --> 01:40:16,979
Pockets ain't empty, cuz.

1070
01:40:21,068 --> 01:40:23,319
And we ain't hungry
no more, right?
